METHODOLOGY:-
Methodology:
1. Overview
The program is designed to manage student records using a singly linked list. It allows the user to perform operations such as adding, viewing, and modifying student details through a menu-driven interface.

2. Data Structure Used
A structure Node is defined to store:

Roll Number
Name
Aadhaar Number
Phone Number
Email

•Each node contains a pointer next to link to the next node.
•A global pointer head is used to store the first node of the list.

3. Working Principle
a) Menu-Driven Execution
The program runs inside a do-while loop.

•A menu is displayed repeatedly until the user selects Exit.
•A switch-case is used to perform operations based on user choice.

b) Adding a Student
A new node is created dynamically using new.
•User inputs all student details.

If the list is empty:
•The new node becomes the head.

Otherwise:
•The list is traversed to the last node.
•The new node is appended at the end.
•This maintains the list in insertion order.

c) Viewing a Student
The user enters a Roll Number.
•The list is traversed from the head node.

Each node is checked:

•If a match is found → student details are displayed.

•If traversal ends without a match → "Student not found" is displayed.
•This operation uses linear search.

d) Modifying a Student
•The user enters a Roll Number.
•The list is traversed sequentially.

If the student is found:
•New details are entered.
•Existing values in the node are updated.

If not found:
"Student not found" message is shown.

4. Memory Management
Memory for each student is allocated dynamically using new.
•Nodes are connected using pointers.

(Note: No deletion operation is implemented.)

5. Program Termination
When the user selects option 4 (Exit):

The loop terminates.

The program ends.

6. Conclusion
The program efficiently manages student records using a linked list, enabling dynamic storage and easy insertion, searching, and updating of records.
